    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix unchecked return values in PNF start thread functions\n\n### Summary\nThe PNF start thread functions `pnf_start_thread` and `pnf_nr_start_thread` were calling `nfapi_pnf_start` and `nfapi_nr_pnf_start` respectively without checking their return values. These functions can return -1 on failure, which was being silently ignored. This could lead to undetected initialization failures in the NFAPI PNF components.\n\nThis fix adds proper error checking and logging for these return values.\n\n### Changes\n- `nfapi/oai_integration/nfapi_pnf.c`: \n  - Added return value checking for `nfapi_pnf_start` in `pnf_start_thread`\n  - Added return value checking for `nfapi_nr_pnf_start` in `pnf_nr_start_thread`\n  - Added error logging when these functions fail\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the issue:\n1. Start the PNF with invalid configuration that causes `nfapi_pnf_start` to fail\n2. Observe that the failure is not detected or logged\n3. The system may appear to start normally but NFAPI communication will not work\n\nWith the fix, when `nfapi_pnf_start` or `nfapi_nr_pnf_start` fails, an error message will be logged indicating the failure and return code, making it easier to diagnose initialization issues.\n"
}